BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 4741.04 be amended and section 5
4741.041 of the Revised Code be enacted to read as follows: 6
Sec. 4741.04. A veterinary-client-patient relationship 7
serves as the basis for interaction between veterinarians, their 8
clients, and their patients. A veterinary-client-patient 9
relationship exists when all of the following conditions have 10
been met: 11
(A) A veterinarian assumes responsibility for making 12
clinical judgments regarding the health of a patient and the 13
need for medical treatment, medical services, or both for the 14
patient, and the client has agreed to follow the veterinarian's 15
instructions regarding the patient. 16
(B) The veterinarian has sufficient knowledge of the 17
patient to initiate at least a general or preliminary diagnosis 18
of the medical condition of the patient. In order to demonstrate 19

