Sec. 4741.041. (A) A licensed veterinarian may conduct 34
telehealth services if all of the following apply: 35
(1) The veterinarian obtains the informed consent from the 36
client, including an acknowledgement that the standards of care 37
prescribed by this chapter equally apply to in-person and 38
telehealth visits. The veterinarian shall maintain documentation 39
of the consent for at least three years after receiving the 40
informed consent. 41
(2) The veterinarian provides the client with the 42
veterinarian's name and contact information and secures an 43
alternate means of contacting the client if the telehealth visit 44
is interrupted. Following the telehealth visit, the veterinarian 45
shall make available to the client an electronic or written 46
record of the visit. The electronic or written record shall 47
include the veterinarian's license number. 48

