(3) Before conducting an evaluation of a patient via a 49
telehealth visit, the veterinarian advises the client of all of 50
the following: 51
(a) The veterinarian may ultimately recommend an in-person 52
visit with the veterinarian or another licensed veterinarian; 53
(b) The veterinarian is prohibited under federal law from 54
prescribing certain drugs or medications based only on a 55
telehealth visit; 56
(c) The appointment for a telehealth visit may be 57
terminated at any time. 58
(B) A licensed veterinarian may prescribe drugs or 59
medications after establishing a veterinary-client-patient 60
relationship via telehealth services, except that all of the 61
following apply: 62
(1) The veterinarian may issue an initial prescription for 63
not more than fourteen days. The veterinarian may issue one 64
refill for not more than fourteen days if the veterinarian sees 65
the patient for another telehealth visit. For additional 66
refills, the patient shall visit the veterinarian in person. 67
(2) The veterinarian shall notify the client that certain 68
prescription drugs or medications may be available at a pharmacy 69
and, if requested, the veterinarian will submit a prescription 70
to a pharmacy of the client's choosing; 71
(3) The veterinarian shall not order, prescribe, or make 72
available a controlled substance, as defined in section 3719.01 73
of the Revised Code, unless the veterinarian has performed an 74
in-person physical examination of the patient. 75
(C) A licensed veterinarian whose client is engaged in any 76

